1 BE I T ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
2 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
3 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 335 of Title 61, unless there is
4 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
5 A. Any person may forage for nuts and edible plants or fungi on
6 state-owned or state-managed property accessible to the public for
7 personal consumption only except when such nuts and other edible
8 plants or fungi are:
9 1. From crops certified by the Oklahoma Agricultural Experiment
10 Station system or the Oklahoma Cooperative Extension Service of the
11 Oklahoma State University Division of Agricultural Sciences and
12 Natural Resources, as provided in Section 8-33 of Title 2 of the
13 Oklahoma Statutes; or
14 2. From plants that are threatened or endangered.
15 B. Any person foraging pursuant to this section is encouraged
16 to:
17 1. Wear an outer garment of hunter orange that is clearly
18 visible while in the field; and
19 2. Recognize which nuts and edible plants or fungi are safe for
20 human consumption.
21 C. As used in this section:
22 1. “State-owned or state-managed property accessible to the
23 public” means property owned or managed by an agency, municipality,
